params:{script:# Import required libraries
from dataiku.scenario import Scenario
from dateutil.relativedelta import relativedelta
import datetime
import dataiku

# Step No: 1 - Initializing Partition Variables for the runs
today = datetime.datetime.now()
# Subtracting days from today in order to account for refresh on source datasets
# For PROMIS refresh lead time is 2 days & data partitioned at YYYY-MM-DD
today = today - relativedelta(days=2)
dailyPart = today.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')   # Override this assignment to prepare for oneoff runs in case of failed runs on specific day

#For HOCCD & IATA data flow we have daily jobs running
#Partitions are handled in Year-Month Fashion
today = datetime.datetime.now() - relativedelta(days=1)
monthlyPart = today.strftime('%Y-%m')   # Override this assignment to prepare for oneoff runs in case of failed runs on specific day
prevmonthlyPart = (today - relativedelta(months=1)).strftime('%Y-%m')   # Override this assignment to prepare for oneoff runs in case of failed runs on specific day
#monthly_partitions='2021-03'

#add variables to the scenario variables 
client = dataiku.api_client()
project = client.get_project(dataiku.default_project_key())
variables = project.get_variables()

variables[\standard\][\dailyPart\] = dailyPart
variables[\standard\][\monthlyPart\] = monthlyPart
variables[\standard\][\prevmonthlyPart\] = prevmonthlyPart

# variable for main flow
project.set_variables(variables)
